President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. will be hosting the Pacific Islands Forum (PIF) leaders at the White House on September 25, 2023, during the second U.S.-Pacific Island Forum (PIF) Summit. The summit will take place from September 25-26. The purpose of the summit is to reaffirm the U.S. commitment to shared regional priorities and deepen cooperation in areas such as climate crisis, economic growth, sustainable development, health security, countering illegal fishing, and people-to-people ties. This summit builds upon last year's U.S.-Pacific Island Country Summit and aims to strengthen the partnership with the Pacific Islands by addressing the challenges of our time.